      "schema:name": "data_path",
      "schema:description": "The top-level directory containing the raw and/or processed data. For a single dataset upload, this might be represented as \".\", whereas for a data upload containing multiple datasets, this would be the directory name for the respective dataset. For example, if the data is within a directory named \"TEST001-RK\", use the syntax \"./TEST001-RK\" for this field. If there are multiple directory levels, use the format \"./TEST001-RK/Run1/Pass2\", where \"Pass2\" is the subdirectory where the single dataset's data is stored. This is an internal metadata field used solely for data ingestion. Example: ./TEST001-RK",
      "pav:createdOn": "2026-03-27T11:10:46-07:00",
